Demonstration of hindexed derived datatype

The same as indexed except that it uses number of bytes instead of number of
elements for displacement array.

    int MPI_Type_create_hindexed(int count, int *array_of_blocklengths,
                                 MPI_Aint *array_of_displacements,
                                 MPI_Datatype oldtype, MPI_Datatype *newtype)

Also, note that the function call is named slightly differently and
displacement array is not of type int but MPI_Aint.

    MPI_Aint disparray[2] = {0, 48}; // no. of bytes difference between
                                     // start of each block
    MPI_Type_create_hindexed(count, blarray, disparray, oldtype, &newtype);
